                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d50">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.6131/8: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-12T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 12, 1917—6 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 13—3:15 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1214. Premier told me Saturday that greatest need now is grain and I was informed
                    today by man who knows, that 3 million quintals, about 11 million bushels, grain
                    were lost or destroyed by army in evacuated territory, that Italy now has food
                    only to last through January. Guns and aeroplanes also greatly needed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
